a:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. IFTTT is best suited for consumers, smart home users, simple automations, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Process Street, meanwhile, shines for operations teams, onboarding, compliance, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2010, IFTTT describes itself as \"Simple conditional automation connecting everyday apps and devices.\" Process Street, established in 2014, positions itself as \"AI-powered workflow and checklist platform for recurring processes.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
b:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Process Street** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (7.0 vs 6.0), more features (8 vs 7). However, this does not mean IFTTT is a poor choice — far from it. IFTTT excels in its own right, particularly for consumers and smart home users.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value excellent for documenting and running processes, go with Process Street. If extremely simple to use matters more to you, IFTTT is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
